{"lemma":"أَجْهِزَةُ","slug":"أَجْهِزَةُ","root":"ج.ه.ز","root_slug":"ج-ه-ز","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ه-ز","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"جِهاز","root":"جهز","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6557","n6558"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AC%D9%92%D9%87%D9%90%D8%B2%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"equipment, device, appliances, outfit, gear, rig"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"implement, utensil, appliance, contrivance, gadget"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"installation, apparatus"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"system, apparatus","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/d͡ʒi.haːz/","/d͡ʒa.haːz/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6557","headword_ar":"جَهَازٌ","root":"jhz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) so accord. to the seven readers in the Kur xii. 59 and 70, (Az, Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jihaAzN","text_ar":"جِهَازٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) but the latter is rare, (Msb,) or bad, (Az, TA,) or an erroneous pronunciation of the people of El-Basrah, (Lth, TA,) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"requisites,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equipments, equipage, furniture, accoutrements,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"apparatus,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) of a bride, [i. e. her"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paraphernalia,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and of a traveller, and of a corpse: (S, Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"provisions and other requisites for a traveller:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 104:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajohizapN","text_ar":"اَجْهِزَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajohizaAtN","text_ar":"اَجْهِزَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b2-  Accord. to some,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Household goods"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"furniture and utensils:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to 'Alee Ibn- 'Eesà,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent goods that are conveyed from country to country:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hence the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jhAz","text_ar":"جهاز"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the bride: (Har p. 104:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent goods that are conveyed as merchandise."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b3-  Also the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is upon a camel that is used for riding"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"consisting of the saddle and its appertenances"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jahaAzihi Daraba fiY","text_ar":"جَهَازِهِ ضَرَبَ فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h [to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (As, S, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took fright and fled"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went away at random, and did not return:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or it is said of a thing that goes away and does not return: (As, S:) originally relating to a camel from whose back the saddle with its apparatus tumbles, falling between his legs, in consequence of which he takes fright and flees or runs away at random, so that he goes away into the land: (As, S, K:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went;"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sAr","text_ar":"سار"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for which in the CK is put"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SAr","text_ar":"صار"},{"kind":"text","text":";) and the meaning of the phrase is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went stumbling upon his apparatus."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) In the T it is said, The Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba AlbaEiyru","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ البَعِيرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY jahaAzihi","text_ar":"فِى جَهَازِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camel took fright and ran away at random, beating the ground with his feet so as to throw down the apparatus and load that were upon him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-  Also the former, The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pudendum of a woman."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Az","Msb","S","K","TA","Lth","As"]},{"entry_id":"n6558","headword_ar":"جِهَازٌ","root":"jhz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jahaAzN","text_ar":"جَهَازٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}